{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7e417b89-482e-425e-a57d-cadd4054195b","content":"The workspace is empty, so I'll answer from general knowledge:\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n-   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**That's it.** MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is the only required change.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of:\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) or run the test exe directly |\n| CLI filters | `--filter` | `--filter` (same syntax supported) |\n| `.runsettings` | Supported | Supported |\n\n### Optional follow-ups:\n- If you use `dotnet test`, add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` for full integration (recommended for SDK 3.8+).\n- If you rely on VSTest-specific adapters/extensions, check for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n- The test binary becomes directly executable (`./MyTests`), which is useful in CI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d56a022-86d7-4ba5-8f31-c408c16fb859","outputTokens":381,"requestId":"BD04:2586A7:1D65D6D:2115C11:6A07C4D5"},"id":"5d23c9a8-c609-4d5d-a28b-5c6dcfcf518a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:05.892Z","parentId":"e4b77115-fae8-4293-b5e1-56478930ecc4"}
